		<h2>Introduction</h2>
		<p>Welcoming a new pet into your home is an exciting time. Whether it's a puppy, kitten, or an older animal, there are certain things you need to keep in mind to ensure they stay healthy and happy. Here are some care tips for new pet parents:</p>

		<h2>Food and Water</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Make sure your pet has access to fresh, clean water at all times.</li>
			<li>Choose a high-quality pet food that is appropriate for your pet's age, size, and activity level.</li>
			<li>Measure out the appropriate portion size to avoid overfeeding.</li>
			<li>Avoid giving your pet table scraps, as they can be harmful to their health.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Exercise</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Regular exercise is important for your pet's physical and mental health.</li>
			<li>Take your dog for walks or runs, or play with your cat using toys.</li>
			<li>Provide plenty of opportunities for your pet to play and explore.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Grooming</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Regular grooming is essential for maintaining your pet's health and hygiene.</li>
			<li>Brush your pet's fur regularly to prevent matting and tangles.</li>
			<li>Trim your pet's nails to prevent them from getting too long.</li>
			<li>Clean your pet's ears and teeth to prevent infections.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Healthcare</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Take your pet to the vet for regular checkups and vaccinations.</li>
			<li>Keep up with flea, tick, and heartworm prevention.</li>
			<li>Be aware of any changes in your pet's behavior or appetite, as they may indicate an underlying health issue</li>
        </ul>
        
